net.sourceforge.waters.analysis
Class ModelChecker

java.lang.Object
  net.sourceforge.waters.analysis.ModelChecker
Direct Known Subclasses:
ControllabilityChecker
public abstract class ModelChecker
extends Object

An abstract class defining the interface of a model checker.

A model checker takes a finite-state machine model as input and performs a particular kind of analysis on it. When done, it returns the result, i.e., whether the particular property checked is true or false. Furthermore, if the property is found not to be satisfied, the model checker provides a counterexample in the form of a sequence of events, explaining why the property that was checked is not satisfied.

To use a model checker, the use first creates an instance of a subclass of this class, and sets up the model to be checked as well as any other parameters that may be needed. Then model checking is started using the run() method. Afterwards results can be queried using the getResult() and getCounterExample() methods. This all can be done with the following code.

ModelChecker checker = new ControllabilityChecker(des); // e.g.
checker.run();
boolean result = checker.getResult();
if (result) {
  // property satisfied ...
} else {
  // property not satisfied ...
  List counterexample = checker.getCounterExample();
}

This class is to be subclassed to implement model checking algorithms for various properties. Each subclass must implement at least the methods run(), getResult(), and getCounterExample().

Robi Malik

Method Detail

run

public abstract boolean run()
Runs this model checker. This method starts the model checking process on the model given as parameter to the constructor of this object. On termination, the result of checking the property is known and can be queried using the getResult() and getCounterExample() methods.

Returns:
true or false to indicate whether the property checked is satisfied or not. The same value can be queried using the getResult() method.

getModel

public ProductDESProxy getModel()
Gets the model under investigation by this model checker.

Returns:
The model checked by this model checker, as passed into its constructor ModelChecker().

getResult

public abstract boolean getResult()
Gets the result of model checking.

Returns:
true if the property checked is satisfied, false otherwise.
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if this method is called before model checking has completed, i.e., before run() has been called.

getCounterExample

public abstract List getCounterExample()
Gets a counterexample if model checking has found that the property checked is not satisfied.

Returns:
A list of events of type EventProxy representing an error trace. The event objects returned must be part of the model that was checked.
Throws:
IllegalStateException - if this method is called before model checking has completed, i.e., before run() has been called, or model checking has found that the property is satisfied and there is no counterexample.
